tic field. Most of these parameters can be remotely measured only via\nradio observations. The ExPRES code provides the proper framework of analysis\nand interpretation for past (Cassini, Voyager, Galileo), current (Juno,\ngroundbased radiotelescopes) and future (BepiColombo, Juice) observations of\nplanetary radio emissions, as well as for future detection of radio emissions\nfrom exoplanetary systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 31 Jan 2019 18:44:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-12"}
